                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A clockwork dragon must use this reaction unless specifically programmed otherwise by its creator;</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> The clockwork dragon is reduced to 0 Hit Points;</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The dragon screeches to a stop and emits a steady, loud ticking sound. At the beginning of what would have been its next turn, the dragon explodes, dealing [[/r 12d10 #piercing]]{12d10 piercing damage} in a 40-foot emanation (<span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"37\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Self-Destruct DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save).</p>\n<p>An adjacent creature can cancel the self-destruct sequence by succeeding at a <span data-pf2-check=\"thievery\" data-pf2-dc=\"37\" data-pf2-traits=\"action:disable-device\" data-pf2-label=\"Cancel Self-Destruct DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Thievery</span> check to Disable a Device.</p>"
